JOHANNEBSURG – This week on Tsonga music icon Papa Penny's reality show, the artist put fans of the show in their place, saying he does not owe anyone good English. Papa Penny said "It's not the English that gets you successful but it's your state of mind and what you're trying to go" The artist said he thought it had thought the word meant something else, only to find out that it meant stupid. Fans took to Twitter to express their feelings on the matter. eNCA